        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 9:03PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne WY</headline>
        <description>At 903 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hawk Springs, or 19 miles southwest of Torrington, moving east at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lyman, Yoder, Huntley, Hawk Springs Reservoir, Southern Hills
Estates, Hawk Springs State Recreation Area, Hawk Springs, Wycross,
and Hawk Springs Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM MDT for
the Panhandle of Nebraska...and southeastern Wyoming.</instruction>
